'''Williams David P<U+00E9>rez Montes''' (born May 21, 1991) is a Venezuelan professional [[baseball]] [[pitcher]] for the [[Atlanta Braves]] of [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB).

==Career==
The Braves added P<U+00E9>rez to the team's 40-man roster on November 19, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bowman|first1=Mark|title=Top prospect Peraza among Braves' roster additions|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/101960388/top-prospect-jose-peraza-among-braves-roster-additions|accessdate=May 7, 2015|publisher=MLB.com|date=November 19, 2014}}</ref>

He was promoted to the major leagues on May 6, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cooper|first1=Jon|title=Braves recall Perez, option Kohn to Triple-A|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/122756274/atlanta-braves-recall-williams-perez-option-michael-kohn-to-triple-a|accessdate=May 7, 2015|publisher=MLB.com|date=May 6, 2015}}</ref> P<U+00E9>rez debuted two days later, yielding two walks, two hits and four runs, while recording one out against the [[Washington Nationals]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cristodero|first1=Damian|title=Perez battles command in big league debut|url=http://m.braves.mlb.com/news/article/123195360/williams-perez-battles-command-in-major-league-debut-for-braves|accessdate=May 9, 2015|publisher=MLB.com|date=May 8, 2015}}</ref>

